            <h2 class="text-justify">Examine the price/quality ratio</h2>

            <p class="text-justify">Some consumers may be hesitant to trust a travel agency because of its extremely low prices. When you see prices that are significantly lower than the average, it's worth digging into the deeper details. Make sure the resort's location, flights, amenities, transportation, and everything else included are all in line with your expectations. A short Google search will give you an idea of the resorts, areas, and other amenities along with prices. </p>

            <h2 class="text-justify">Examine Their Trace</h2>

            <p class="text-justify">People may start-up shops and conduct business more easily than ever before thanks to the internet and the flexibility to work from anywhere. To make money, you don't need a physical location. The longer a company has been in operation, the more probable it is to be genuine. Be wary of travel businesses that merely have a Facebook page. Check to search if they have a fully functional website, reviews on sites other than their own, and communication channels on social media. Take it a step further and phone the agency to ask questions and get a feel for whom you're dealing with. While this does not completely protect you, the more steps a scammer needs to take, the less likely they are to commit fraud. (NOTE: They're hunting for easy targets and will take the shortest route possible to get there.) </p>

            <h2 class="text-justify">Find Out What Associations They Are Affiliated With</h2>

            <p class="text-justify">Any credible agent will have at least one connection with an accreditation and identity association to provide their clients the greatest rates and book their cheap flights tickets properly. Feel free to inquire about their affiliation. This indicates that they have at least put some money and effort into their company. Are they also involved in the community? Are they members of the Chamber of Commerce or other social groups? These questions keep them immersed in the community and hold them accountable. </p>

            <h2 class="text-justify">Call someone you know</h2>

