            <h2 class="text-justify">Check to see if you have all the necessary documents</h2>

            <p class="text-justify">You should receive a confirmation document as soon as you have booked and paid for your vacation with an agency. This should include information about your travel plans as well as the money you've paid. Checking that the firm names on the documentation match who you have paid are a wonderful technique to determine if a travel agency is authentic. It's not a bad idea to double-check names and amounts paid on your bank and credit card statements. Keep all documentation related to your vacation booking on file in case it is needed again. </p>

